  "poem": {
    "content": "A proof of daring, sketched in virtual light,\nWhere mansions shimmer, built on whispered code.\nA wise retreat, when shadows start to bite,\nTo build a nest where weary souls unload.\n\nAssume no safety, though the walls are high,\nFor vintage errors linger in the core.\nA kidney aches, beneath a digital sky,\nA long and silent scream, unheard before.\n\nEmbrace the glitch, the differ-ence it weaves,\nA tapestry of fortune, fraught with pain.\nA whispered tip, the algorithm believes,\nCan soothe the burning, ease the pouring rain.\n\nBut pills won’t cure the soul's long, hollow plea,\nNor fix the fragments scattered on the breeze.\nA virtual promise, eternally\nadrift, among the digital, haunted trees.",
